Deep Learning – Image Classification (MNIST)

📄 Description

Built a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) model to classify digits (0–9) from the MNIST dataset using TensorFlow.

📁 Files

mnist_image_classifier.ipynb

Accuracy/loss graphs (inline in notebook)

🧠 Dataset

MNIST – Handwritten digits dataset from Keras

🧪 Steps Performed

Loaded MNIST dataset

Normalized pixel values

Built a CNN model using Keras

Trained and validated the model

Plotted accuracy and loss curves

🛠️ Libraries Used

tensorflow / keras

numpy

matplotlib

✅ Output

Validation Accuracy: ~98%

Visual performance metrics
